gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Bucks 143, Kings 142
gameRecap.excerpt: Damian Lillard made a game-winning 3PT FG as time expired in overtime as the Bucks defeated the Kings, 143-142. Damian Lillard led the Bucks with 29 points and eight assists as Giannis Antetokounmpo totaled his fifth triple-double of the year (40th of career) with 27 points, 10 rebounds, and 10 assists. Malik Beasley (23 points, 5-9 3PT) and Bobby Portis (22 points, 10 rebounds) had strong performances for Milwaukee as well. De’Aaron Fox led Sacramento with 32 points and five assists as Malik Monk (28 points, seven rebounds, seven assists) and Domantas Sabonis (21 points (9-10 FG), 13 rebounds, 15 assists) totaled 49 points. Milwaukee wins their third straight game to improve to 28-12 as the Kings move to 23-16.
